## Overview
Banners in Minecraft are highly customizable. Using `BannerMeta`, you can add colors, patterns, and even custom names.

### Creating a Simple Banner
```java
import org.bukkit.Material;
import org.bukkit.entity.Player;
import org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack;
import org.bukkit.inventory.meta.BannerMeta;
import org.bukkit.DyeColor;

public void giveSimpleBanner(Player player) {
    ItemStack banner = new ItemStack(Material.WHITE_BANNER);
    BannerMeta meta = (BannerMeta) banner.getItemMeta();
    meta.setDisplayName("§aMy First Banner");
    banner.setItemMeta(meta);
    player.getInventory().addItem(banner);
}
```

### Giving the Banner via Command
```java
if (command.getName().equalsIgnoreCase("givebanner")) {
    giveSimpleBanner(player);
    player.sendMessage("§aYou received a custom banner!");
}
```

## Overview
Banners support multiple patterns and colors.

### Adding a Pattern
```java
import org.bukkit.block.banner.Pattern;
import org.bukkit.block.banner.PatternType;

BannerMeta meta = (BannerMeta) banner.getItemMeta();
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(DyeColor.RED, PatternType.STRIPE_TOP));
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(DyeColor.BLUE, PatternType.CIRCLE_MIDDLE));
banner.setItemMeta(meta);
```

## Overview
Combine colors, patterns, and names to make highly customized banners.

### Full Example
```java
ItemStack banner = new ItemStack(Material.BLACK_BANNER);
BannerMeta meta = (BannerMeta) banner.getItemMeta();
meta.setDisplayName("§5Guild Banner");
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(DyeColor.WHITE, PatternType.BORDER));
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(DyeColor.RED, PatternType.CREEPER));
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(DyeColor.YELLOW, PatternType.RHOMBUS_MIDDLE));
banner.setItemMeta(meta);
player.getInventory().addItem(banner);
player.sendMessage("§aYou received the Guild Banner!");
```

## Overview
You can generate banners dynamically based on player input or events.

### Example: Banner Based on Player Team Color
```java
import org.bukkit.scoreboard.Team;
Team team = player.getScoreboard().getEntryTeam(player.getName());
DyeColor color = DyeColor.WHITE;
if (team != null) {
    switch(team.getName()) {
        case "RedTeam": color = DyeColor.RED; break;
        case "BlueTeam": color = DyeColor.BLUE; break;
    }
}
ItemStack banner = new ItemStack(Material.BANNER);
BannerMeta meta = (BannerMeta) banner.getItemMeta();
meta.addPattern(new Pattern(color, PatternType.STRIPE_DOWNRIGHT));
banner.setItemMeta(meta);
player.getInventory().addItem(banner);
player.sendMessage("§aYour team banner has been created!");
```
